                                               'mission: To accelerate the '
                                               'transition to a clean, '
                                               'affordable, and reliable '
                                               'electric grid through '
                                               'technical assistance and '
                                               'policy advocacy.\n'
                                               'keyActivities: - Modeling and '
                                               'analysis of clean energy '
                                               'transitions in electricity '
                                               'systems\n'
                                               '- Technical assistance to '
                                               'policymakers on grid '
                                               'decarbonization strategies\n'
                                               '- Research on renewable energy '
                                               'integration and grid '
                                               'reliability\n'
                                               '- Economic analysis of clean '
                                               'electricity system costs and '
                                               'benefits\n'
                                               '- Policy advocacy for '
                                               'competitive wholesale '
                                               'electricity markets\n'
                                               '- Analysis of environmental '
                                               'and health impacts of power '
                                               'sector emissions\n'
                                               '- Workforce development '
                                               'strategies for the clean '
                                               'energy transition\n'
                                               'potentialRisks_0: Operational '
                                               'risk: Potential resource '
                                               'constraints due to reliance on '
                                               'a network of external experts '
                                               'and partners for analysis and '
                                               'modeling\n'
                                               'potentialRisks_1: Strategic '
                                               'risk: Possible mission drift '
                                               'if expanding scope beyond core '
                                               'focus on grid modeling and '
                                               'clean energy transition\n'
                                               'potentialRisks_2: Reputational '
                                               'risk: Maintaining credibility '
                                               'and neutrality while working '
                                               'with diverse stakeholders in '
                                               'the energy sector\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2020_0: The 90% '
                                               'Clean case supports '
                                               'approximately 29 million '
                                               'job-years cumulatively during '
                                               '20202035.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2020_1: The 90% '
                                               'Clean case avoids about $1.2 '
                                               'trillion in environmental and '
                                               'health costs through 2050.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2020_2: By '
                                               '2030, the United States can '
                                               'reach over 70% zero-carbon '
                                               'electricity on the grid at no '
                                               'additional cost.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2020_3: '
                                               'Achieving 90% clean '
                                               'electricity by 2035 would '
                                               'contribute a 27% reduction in '
                                               'economy-wide carbon emissions '
                                               'from 2010 levels.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2020_4: The 90% '
                                               'Clean case results in an 88% '
                                               'reduction in carbon dioxide '
                                               'emissions by 2035 compared to '
                                               'the No New Policy case.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_0: '
                                               'Renewables in ERCOT generated '
                                               'approximately 47 TWh of energy '
                                               'over the summer of 2023, '
                                               'accounting for about 25% of '
                                               'all electricity consumed.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_1: The '
                                               'estimated total benefits from '
                                               'renewables in ERCOT during the '
                                               'summer of 2023 amounted to '
                                               'about $1.9 billion, including '
                                               'wholesale electricity price '
                                               'reductions, reduced water use, '
                                               'and reduced emissions.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_2: '
                                               'Renewables reduced water '
                                               'withdrawals by approximately '
                                               '665 billion gallons over the '
                                               'summer of 2023, equating to '
                                               'the annual water use of about '
                                               '7.3 million Texans.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_3: '
                                               'Renewables saved approximately '
                                               '31.3 million tons of CO2 '
                                               'emissions during the summer of '
                                               '2023, representing about 5% of '
                                               'the total annual CO2 emissions '
                                               'of Texas.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_4: Avoided '
                                               'NOx emissions were estimated '
                                               'at about 19.8 thousand tons '
                                               'over the summer of 2023, '
                                               'translating to an approximate '
                                               'value of $94.3 million.\n'

                                               'outcomeMetrics_2021_0: The '
                                               'ICCT contributed to the '
                                               'reduction of billions of tons '
                                               'of carbon dioxide and the '
                                               'prevention of thousands of '
                                               'premature deaths over the next '
                                               'decade and beyond through '
                                               'their regulatory efforts.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2021_1: '
                                               'Approximately 3.5 million '
                                               'electric vehicles were sold in '
                                               'China in 2021, accounting for '
                                               '51% of the global total.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2021_2: To '
                                               'support a stock of 26 million '
                                               'electric vehicles in the '
                                               'United States by 2030, public '
                                               'and workplace charging needs '
                                               'to grow from approximately '
                                               '216,000 chargers in 2020 to '
                                               '2.4 million by 2030, requiring '
                                               'an investment of $28 billion.\n'
                                               "outcomeMetrics_2021_3: ICCT's "
                                               'research indicated that '
                                               'zero-emission heavy-duty '
                                               'vehicles accounted for close '
                                               'to 90% of cumulative '
                                               'zero-emission heavy-duty '
                                               'vehicle sales between 2010 and '
                                               '2020 in Europe.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2021_4: In '
                                               'Latin America, leaders Chile '
                                               'and Colombia had over 2000 '
                                               'electric buses on order or on '
                                               'the streets by the end of '
                                               '2021.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2022_0: ICCT '
                                               'researchers studied electric '
                                               'vehicle deployment in '
                                               'Southeast Asia, focusing on '
                                               'electric two- and '
                                               'three-wheeler transport, fuel '
                                               'efficiency standards, and '
                                               'sustainable fuels.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2022_1: ICCT '
                                               'researchers assessed '
                                               'national-level taxation and '
                                               'subsidy policies for passenger '
                                               'vehicles across 18 Asian and '
                                               'Asia-Pacific countries, '
                                               'indicating that reductions in '
                                               'one-time taxes could '
                                               'significantly reduce ownership '
                                               'costs for efficient vehicles.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2022_2: In '
                                               '2022, ICCT researchers '
                                               'evaluated the effectiveness of '
                                               'policies in curtailing '
                                               'emissions from heavy-duty '
                                               'vehicles in China, emphasizing '
                                               'the importance of integrated '
                                               'emissions control regulation '
                                               'for both pollutants and '
                                               'greenhouse gases.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2022_3: ICCT '
                                               'provided analysis to inform '
                                               'the next phase of emission '
                                               'standards for light- and '
                                               'heavy-duty vehicles in Europe, '
                                               'aiming for a reduction of at '
                                               'least 60% in 2030 and a target '
                                               'of at least 90% for 2035.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2022_4: '
                                               'Research in Latin America '
                                               'showed that electric vehicle '
                                               'adoption, although at an early '
                                               'stage, is underway with '
                                               'significant advances in '
                                               'electric bus fleets in Chile '
                                               'and Colombia.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_0: In '
                                               '2023, the ICCT published 199 '
                                               'research papers and blog '
                                               'posts.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_1: The '
                                               'organization organized 25 '
                                               'webinars, which included video '
                                               'content.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_2: The '
                                               'Global Automaker Rating 2022 '
                                               'evaluated and rated 20 '
                                               'manufacturers on their '
                                               'progress towards zero-emission '
                                               'vehicles.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_3: ICCT '
                                               'supported technical assistance '
                                               'in Southeast Asia to '
                                               'accelerate the deployment of '
                                               'electric buses.\n'
                                               'outcomeMetrics_2023_4: In '
                                               'Guangdong province, China, '
                                               'zero-emission logistics trucks '
                                               'experienced strong growth and '
                                               'commercialization.\n'
